<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-01T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-01T18:00:00-05:00" n="495" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">800.24/8–145: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Berle</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-01T19:00:00-04:00">August 1,
                                    1945—7 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1897. Presidential Directive interpreting prior Directive of July 5, 1945
                            has been issued to JCS. With respect to Brazil interpretation
                            specifically authorizes as lend-leasable the hospitalization of wounded,
                            transport of Brazilian Expeditionary Force to Brazil, return of military
                            personnel being trained in the US, transfers for naval and air patrols,
                            transfers to be used directly in support of redeployment (air sea
                            rescue, ATC installations, weather stations), transfers for equipping
                            forces participating directly in the Pacific Theater.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>